  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200°C/ 180°C (fan)/ gas 6, then take your <strong>steak</strong> out of the fridge, open the packet and let it adjust to room temperature</p><p>Peel and slice your <strong>brown onion[s]<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span></strong>and slice your <strong>potatoes</strong> (skins on) into discs and add them to a baking tray (or two!) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong>, then put the tray[s]<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>in the oven for 10-15 min or until they have softened</p><p>Tip: You don't want the potatoes to brown at this point!</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2368Step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2368Step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2368Step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2368Step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2368Step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p><p>While the potatoes are cooking, trim your<strong> green beans</strong>, then add them to a pot with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cover them with <strong>boiled water </strong>(just enough to cover them)</p><p>Bring to the boil over a high heat and cook for 3-4 min or until tender</p><p>Once tender, drain and rinse the beans under <strong>cold water</strong> and set aside for later</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2368Step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2368Step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2368Step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2368Step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2368Step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Peel and finely slice (don't chop!) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Dissolve your <strong>beef stock mix</strong> and your <strong>redcurrant jelly</strong> in 150ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[195ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[250ml]</span> <strong>boiled water </strong>and set it aside for later – this is your<strong> redcurrant stock</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2368Step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2368Step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2368Step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2368Step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2368Step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Warm [80ml] <span class=\"text-purple\">[120ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[160ml] </span><strong>milk</strong> in the <strong>microwave </strong>and stir through your <strong>clotted cream</strong> – this is your <strong>clotted cream mixture</strong></p><p>Once the potatoes have softened, layer the <strong>sliced potatoes</strong> and <strong>onion</strong> in an <strong>oven-proof dish</strong> and season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong>, then pour your <strong>clotted cream mixture</strong> all over and sprinkle with your<strong> grated Italian hard cheese</strong></p><p>Put the dish in the oven for 15 min or until golden and crisp – these are your <strong>dauphinoise potatoes</strong></p><p>Meanwhile, heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) over a high heat</p>",
      "order": 4,
